    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="713" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                <head>Inhabitants of Canzo</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]<lb/>[Extract.]</note>
                <dateline>No. 106 <hi rend="smallcaps">Congress Street</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Brooklyn, L. I.</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-07-20">
                        <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 20, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>I have the honor of informing you that the citizens of Canzo, Province of
                        Como, Lombardy, Italy, wishing to express their veneration and sympathy for
                        the great martyr to the cause of emancipation and the Union, our lamented
                        President, Abraham Lincoln, unanimously passed a resolution to call after
                        his name the new square by the side of the national road in their town. They
                        wished their resolution should reach your Excellency’s hands, and intrusted
                        to me the care of fulfilling their desire.</p>
                <p> * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>Please receive my highest feelings of regard, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ACHILLE MAGNI</signed>.</closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>His Excellency <hi rend="smallcaps">Andrew Johnson</hi>, <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">President of the United States of America</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
